            <accessrestrict id="aspace_a1033a41b509c80221d3aa675db44c61">
               <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
               <p>The scrapbook requires the assistance of staff of Manuscripts and Archives because of the fragility of the fold-out inserts, especially the maps.</p>
            </accessrestrict>
            <scopecontent id="aspace_3cc3e516b1b5d19def9ba4cef223768d">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>The scrapbook contains handwritten accounts for sugar, cotton, and tobacco kept by Day's newspaper clippings; several broadsides, including ones for the Cuban Lottery (1860) and the new Orleans Lottery (1839); a hand-drawn plan of Dat's room; and other printed ephemera. It also contains three folded maps in extremely fragile condition: military map of parts of Kansas, Nebraska, and Dakota by G. K. Warren, from explorations (1855-1857); map of Pilot Knob, Missouri; and map of the Hudson River (1830).</p>
               <p>This accession is not available on microfilm.</p>
            </scopecontent>
